text: Maurice J. McDonough High School is a high school or secondary school in Maryland, United States and is run through the Charles County Public Schools system. It has approximately 1,230 students and 80 employees. The school, built in 1976, is named for Maurice James McDonough, who was an early educator in Charles County, Maryland. ==Sports== 2A State football champions in 2010, coached by Luke Ethington. ==Notes== ==External links== * Category:Public high schools in Maryland Category:Schools in Charles County, Maryland Category:Educational institutions established in 1977 Category:1977 establishments in Maryland
